			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				&lt;nods&gt;<BR>
<BR>
Got mine off a sentry too.  I am beginning to think that the Jarsath armor is not a random drop off of ANY mob... I now believe that each piece will randomly drop off of a different specific mob...  This is my conclusion based upon the 30 or so hours I've spent to date in Karnors.  <BR>
On another note, do not believe the bs you hear about being able to just waltz into Karnor's as a newbie and get a full suit of Jarsath because &quot;high lvls just leave it rotting on the corpses&quot;.  This is simply not true.  All of these drops are uncommon.  No, they are not common.  No matter who says that, don't buy it.  They simply are not.  They're uncommon, with some being rare.  And unless you can cast invis on yourself you will not get the chance to loot anything more than 1 or so of these armor pieces (as most of these items require you to go deeper into Karnors to get them as opposed to just hanging around the zone line).  Moreover, when these items DO drop, rest assured someone in the group that took the mob down WILL loot the item in question(the armor is why many high lvls come to Karnor's in the first place), and if they don't, then a higher lvl character will beat you to it when the group that killed the mob does a &quot;/shout Jarsath Vambraces near such and such! &quot;<BR>
I spent over 12 hours in this zone as a 27 shaman trying to get the mythical &quot;full suit&quot; of Jarsath.  Learn from my words, and don't bother till you're higher lvl.  True, I got a piece of Jarsath out of all of that (the helm of course), but was it worth the 2 bubs of exp I lost dying due to trains?  NO.<BR>
<BR>
Peace,<BR>
Emrak<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
